messages.message:
Not sure if this is the right channel but am I the only one that gets an error when going to ib.com (http://ib.com) with the main page?

```ib_shared.bundle.js?v=1665507633.0103343:99 /api/v1/drives/system/global/fs/Instabase Drive/System/Desktop/Background/ failed with message: Error occurred executing GRPC method: Request /file_service.FileService/ListDir failed. Error code=NOT_FOUND, Error=(5, 'not found'), Message: Folder System/Desktop/Background does not exist: <nil>. Non-retriable error.. retrying 0 more times```
This has been here for at least a month or so and it messes up the main page for me in that I can’t click on the “all apps” button until I go into “file explorer” or any other app.

Hey Will, that error should be harmless (although I do want to make it not appear 3 times...). It's looking for a custom background, not finding one, so it should be falling back to the default and loading desktop-background.jpg - do you have that in your network requests?

Can you explain what you mean when you say you can't click on the all apps button? Is the overlay not working? Can you try hard refreshing maybe, cmd+shift+r? Everything is working fine for me.

Hi Jessica, thanks for responding. I did a hard refresh which is still showing the same result.

I see two fetches for background in network, both seem to be the same (image attached).

When I click the apps button, nothing happens. Much like if there was nothing attached to it.

For custom background, I thought that might be the issue but I don’t have anything in there and the button is disabled.
Also, I’m not admin any more on ib.com (http://ib.com), could this be causing an issue in trying to load that image? Did anything change with our permissions and how they get handled?

I just logged in on a non-admin account and am still seeing the background. Are you sure you're not an admin though? That custom desktop background is a site-wide config and is only visible to site admins.

I don't see any requests in your screenshot for desktop-background.jpg.... strange!

Is anyone else seeing this on prod?
maybe I’m an admin as part of being in the company group?
i just checked and your <mailto:will.davis@instabase.com|will.davis@instabase.com> account is not an admin
can you take a screenshot of the bottom rows of your network tab like this?
@Serena is this what you are looking for?
that still doesn’t solve the mystery about why we see different behavior from you, though, even though we’re all using non-admin accounts :disappointed:
